<section class="content" id="research">
    <p class="heading-1 container">SIM: The Social Robot</p>
    <div class="flex-grid container">
        <div class="fg--cell content--text center">
            <p>We had done the groundwork, were super inspired, and had our research question and hypotheses - but we needed a way to test them. We build <em>SIM</em> - our prototype of a socially intelligent robot. SIM can engage in <em>affective interchanges</em> with people by <em>understanding</em> and <em>expressing</em> emotions. It's behavior is governed by what we call the Social Interaction Model.</p>

            <p>Built on theories of human emotion from psychology, behavioral sciences and human-robot interaction, the SIM table is essentially a <em>map</em> of situations, emotions, behaviors, and functions. The SIM table defines how SIM would <em>react to an emotional stimulus</em> in a given situation, and how that emotional response would <em>affect the dynamics</em> of that interaction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fg--cell--custom">
            <picture class="content-image">
                <img class="no-shadow" src="img/sim/sim-table.png" alt="The SIM table" />
                {# <div class="picture-tag"></div> #}
            </picture>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="content alt" id="design-01">
    <p class="heading-1 container">Designing the Robot</p>
    <div class="flex-grid container">
        <div class="fg--cell content--text center">
            <p>Knowing what emotions SIM needed to express before-hand made it much easier to work out the design and technical details.</p>

            <p>For the body, we used three motors - two for the head and one for the body. This gave us enough <em>flexibility</em> to design expressive movements. We mounted an android powered phone for SIM's head, giving us <em>a blank canvas</em> to design SIM's face on.</p>

            <p>For the facial design, we wanted to keep things simple and as universally understandable as possible. I designed SIM's face to be <em>minimal, but super versatile</em>, so SIM's expressions are <em>exaggerated</em> and easily understandable.</p>
        </div>
